      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/57b2e6/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2022-01-19T10:50:48.576Z",
      "cooked": "<p>It depends on the device. The first BLE devices only supported one device connection. More recent BLE (or dual BLE/ANT+) support 2 BLE channels and let you connect 2 different devices simultaneously in BLE.<br>\nThe Polar H10 for example supports the 2 BLE connections if you have enabled that in the settings. I have it paired in Bluetooth mode to my Edge 830 and my Samsung phone running Fatmaxxer for DFA-A1 in real-time. I wanted my Edge to record HR in BLE because that\u2019s better for RR interval recording. That way I can do post-ride analysis for DFA-A1 as well.<br>\nStill can\u2019t find a decent answer on the BLE capabilities for the Assioma\u2019s\u2026</p>",
