      "created_at": "2022-01-19T13:29:33.403Z",
      "cooked": "<p>No, there are a number of BLE 4 devices that allow two devices to connect. In some cases, 2 apps running on the same phone count as one connection. But sometimes they are considered 2 connections. So it\u2019s a bit trial and error.<br>\nBut ANT+ is way more flexible with that. The signal can be picked up by a limitless number of devices\u2026</p>",
